1) It is possible to complete the professional practice in one semester at one institution. To do this, register for the "Professional Practice of Linguistics" subject. If you want to start the practice in the middle of the semester or e.g. in the summer, write to the practice lecturer Ann Siiman (ann.siiman@ut.ee).
2) Complete a practice portfolio during the entire MA studies at several institutions. To do this, write to the practice lecturer Ann Siiman (ann.siiman@ut.ee). You do not need to register for the subject if you plan the work-activities needed to complete the practice for a longer period than one semester.

The list of practice places, the practice diary and portfolio, etc. can be found in the "Keeleteaduse praktika" Moodle study guide ("Õpijuhis"). Everyone can access Moodle, it is not necessary to be registered for the subject or Moodle.Objectives/eesmärkid:  - improve their knowledge and skills in linguistics speciality and across specialties as well as skills related to self-directed learning and social skills, for example finding a practice position - to acquire practical work experience in linguistics outside of the university or, as an exception, in one of its units -  become more aware of career development opportunities in linguistics and in the wider field of arts and humanitiesLearning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After completing the practice, the student is able to: - know the components of the practice (supervisor, agreement before the practice, the practice diary or portfolio, report of the practice - apply the knowledge and skills acquired in linguistics in the work environment, taking into account its special requirements; - complete practical training tasks in an organized and purposeful manner, can manage his/her practice time - give feedback to his/her supervisor, analyze and apply the feedback given by the supervisor - analyze the linguistic practice experience in the context of his/her studies and career development and value practical training as part of the learning process.
